# Version Management

When committing and pushing changes, always bump the patch version in `pyproject.toml`.

The version is located at `tool.poetry.version` in `pyproject.toml`. For example, if the current version is `0.70.3`, bump it to `0.70.4`.

This ensures every commit pushed to the repository has a unique version number for tracking and deployment purposes.

# Testing Requirements

**Before committing and pushing ANY changes, you MUST run the full test suite.**

## Quick Test Command (Use This!)

```bash
make test
```

This runs ALL tests: unit tests, backend tests, and E2E integration tests with emulators.

## Manual Test Commands (if make isn't available)

1. **Unit tests (karaoke_gen package) - 70% coverage required:**
```bash
poetry run pytest tests/unit/ -v --cov=karaoke_gen --cov-report=term-missing --cov-fail-under=70
```

2. **Backend unit tests:**
```bash
poetry run pytest backend/tests/ --ignore=backend/tests/emulator -v
```

3. **E2E integration tests with emulators:**
```bash
./scripts/start-emulators.sh
export FIRESTORE_EMULATOR_HOST=127.0.0.1:8080
export STORAGE_EMULATOR_HOST=http://127.0.0.1:4443
export GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT=test-project
poetry run pytest backend/tests/emulator/ -v
./scripts/stop-emulators.sh
```

## Pre-commit Checklist

- [ ] All unit tests pass (`make test-unit`)
- [ ] All backend tests pass (`make test-backend`)
- [ ] E2E integration tests pass (`make test-e2e`)
- [ ] Coverage is at least 70%
- [ ] Version in `pyproject.toml` has been bumped

**Do not commit or push code that fails tests. Fix any test failures before proceeding.**
